    <p style="font-size:1.4em">VirES for Swarm</p>
    <p>
      <i>VirES for Swarm</i> is an interactive web interface for visualization of the <a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/missions/swarm" target="_blank">Swarm mission</a> products officially released by the European Space Agency.  It includes tools for studying various geomagnetic models by comparing them to the Swarm satellite measurements at given space weather and ionospheric conditions.
    </p>
    <p>
      In addition to this interactive web interface, users can also explore the data in
      <a target="_blank" href="https://swarm-vre.readthedocs.io/en/latest/intro.html">Jupyter-based</a>
      <a target="_blank" href="https://vre.vires.services"><i>Virtual Reseach Environmet</i> (VRE)</a>
      or on their own computer via the <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/readme.html">Python client</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Selected datasets can be also accessed via the <a target="_blank" href="/hapi">Heliophysics Application Programming Interface (HAPI)</a>.
    </p>

    <p style="font-size:1.4em">Data</p>

          <p>Data from the following Swarm products are available in VirES:</p>
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The low resolution (1Hz) magnetic VFM vector and ASM scalar data (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-1b-product-definitions#MAGX_LR_1B_Product">MAGx_LR_1B</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The high resolution (50Hz) magnetic VFM vector data (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-1b-product-definitions#Magnetic_Products">MAGx_HR_1B</a>,
              accessible via the <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/available_parameters.html#collections">Python client</a>,
              readily available in <a target="_blank" href="https://vre.vires.services">VRE</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The plasma data (2Hz) from the Langmuir probe including electron temperature and plasma density (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-1b-product-definitions#EFIX_LP_1B_Product">EFIx_LP_1B</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The ionospheric bubble index data (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#IBIxTMS_2F">IBIxTMS_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The ionospheric total electron content data (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#TECxTMS_2F">TECxTMS_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The single and combined S/C solution for the current density data
              (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#FACxTMS_2F">FACxTMS_2F</a> and
              <a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#FAC_TMS_2F">FAC_TMS_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The dayside equatorial electric field data (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#EEFxTMS_2F">EEFxTMS_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The characteristics of the plasma density and plasma irregularities along the orbit (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#IPDxIRR_2F">IPDxIRR_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               High-latitude ionospheric horizontal sheet current densities profiles calculated using
               the Line Current (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-AEBS-product-definition.pdf">AEJxLPL_2F</a>)
               and Spherical Elementary Current Systems (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-AEBS-product-definition.pdf">AEJxLPS_2F</a>) methods
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               High-latitude ionospheric horizontal sheet current boundaries and peaks locations calculated using
               the Line Current (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-AEBS-product-definition.pdf">AEJxPBL_2F</a>)
               and Spherical Elementary Current Systems (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-AEBS-product-definition.pdf">AEJxPBS_2F</a>) methods
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               Aurora oval boundaries derived from the Field-Aligned Currents data
               (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-AEBS-product-definition.pdf">AOBxFAC_2F</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               Mid-latitude ionospheric trough (MIT) boundaries and minima based on the Langmuir probe electron density and temperature measurements
               (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-PRISM-Product-Definition.pdf">MITx_LP_2F</a>),
               accessible via the <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/available_parameters.html#collections">Python client</a>.
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               Mid-latitude ionospheric trough (MIT) boundaries and minima derived from the GPS TEC estimate
               (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-PRISM-Product-Definition.pdf">MITxTEC_2F</a>),
               accessible via the <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/available_parameters.html#collections">Python client</a>.
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               Midnight plasma-pause index (PPI) and the associated SSFAC boundaries
               (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/Swarm-PRISM-Product-Definition.pdf">PPIxFAC_2F</a>),
               accessible via the <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/available_parameters.html#collections">Python client</a>.
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
               Swarm spacecrafts' positions (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/missions/swarm/product-data-handbook/level-1b-product-definitions#Ephemeris_Products">MODx_SC_1B</a>)
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>The VirES API also provides access to:</a>
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Hourly, 1 minute and 1 second ground magnetic observatory data (AUX_OBS) from
              <a target="_blank" href="https://intermagnet.org/index-eng.php">INTERMAGNET</a> and
              <a target="_blank" href="https://wdc.bgs.ac.uk/">WDC</a>
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              1 and 4 months Virtual Observatory data (VOBS) from the
              <a href="https://www.space.dtu.dk/english/research/projects/project-descriptions/geomagnetic-virtual-observatories" target="_blank">GVO project</a>.
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Vector magnetic field measurements acquired by the CryoSat-2, GRACE and GRACE-FO missions.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            These datasets can be accessed with the
            <a target="_blank" href="https://viresclient.readthedocs.io/en/latest/available_parameters.html#collections">VirES Python client</a>,
            readily available in <a target="_blank" href="https://vre.vires.services">VRE</a>.
          </p>

          <p>The following models of the Earth's magnetic field and its components (core, crust, lithospheric, magnetospheric, and ionospheric magnetic field) are available</p>
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The 13th generation of the International Geomagnetic Reference Field (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth-planets-space.springeropen.com/articles/10.1186/s40623-020-01288-x">IGRF 13</a>) released in December 2019 by the International Association of Geomagnetism and Aeronomy
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The CHAOS-7 high resolution geomagnetic field model derived from Swarm, CHAMP, Ã˜rsted, SAC-C and Cryosat satellite magnetic data along with ground observatory data (<a target="_blank" href="https://spacecenter.dk/files/magnetic-models/CHAOS-7/">CHAOS-7</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the main (core) field and its temporal variation (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MCO_SHA_2C">MCO_SHA_2C</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the main (core) field and its temporal variation (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MCO_SHA_2D">MCO_SHA_2D</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the lithospheric field (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MLI_SHA_2C">MLI_SHA_2C</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the lithospheric field (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MLI_SHA_2D">MLI_SHA_2D</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The LCS-1 high-resolution lithospheric field model, derived from CHAMP and Swarm satellite observations (<a target="_blank" href="https://spacecenter.dk/files/magnetic-models/LCS-1/">LCS-1</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The MF7 crustal field model, derived from CHAMP satellite observations (<a target="_blank" href="https://geomag.us/models/MF7.html">MF7</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the lithospheric field (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/missions/swarm/product-data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MLI_SHA_2E">MLI_SHA_2E</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the large-scale magnetospheric field and its Earth-induced counterpart (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MMA_SHA_2C">MMA_SHA_2C primary and secondary field</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the large-scale magnetospheric field and its Earth-induced counterpart (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MMA_SHA_2F">MMA_SHA_2F primary and secondary field</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The <a target="_blank" href="https://spacecenter.dk/files/magnetic-models/CHAOS-7/">CHAOS</a> spherical harmonic model of the large-scale magnetospheric field and its Earth-induced counterpart (CHAOS-MMA primary and secondary field)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the daily geomagnetic variation at middle latitudes (Sq) and low latitudes (EEJ) (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MIO_SHA_2C">MIO_SHA_2C primary and secondary field</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Spherical harmonic model of the daily geomagnetic variation at middle latitudes (Sq) and low latitudes (EEJ) (<a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/web/guest/missions/esa-eo-missions/swarm/data-handbook/level-2-product-definitions#MIO_SHA_2D">MIO_SHA_2D primary and secondary field</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Model of the associated magnetic field of the ionospheric current system (<a target="_blank" href="https://pyamps.readthedocs.io/en/latest/readme.html">AMPS</a>)
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>Users can also work with Custom Models and upload own Spherical Harmonic Expansion coefficients (<a target="_blank" href="https://spacecenter.dk/files/magnetic-models/CHAOS-5/SHC-Format-Decsription.pdf">SHC file format</a>)</p>

          <p>The global context of space weather is provided in form of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The Disturbance storm time index (<a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disturbance_storm_time_index">Dst Index</a>) and its rate of change.
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The disturbances in the horizontal component of the Earth's magnetic field (<a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K-index">planetary Kp Index</a>)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              Observed daily measure of the solar radio flux per unit frequency at a wavelength of 10.7 cm
              (<a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_cycle#Solar_radio_flux">F10.7 index</a>) read from
              the auxiliary <a target="_blank" href="https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/documents/20142/37627/swarm-level-2-product-specification.pdf/2979b351-b6a2-69b6-8539-9ed9f32984f0">AUX_F10_2_</a> product.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            The data accessible on VirES consists of the newest versions available and any new data will appear within 4 hours after being published.
          </p>

